Routing
1. add a forward slash in the header tag of the index.html like so ( <base href="/">)
2. configure the routes. state the path and corresponding component.
3. pass the defined routed as an argument for the forRoot method of the router module.
4. export the appRoutingModule and routingComponents
5.  import it in the app module and include it in the import array and declarations array.
congrats! you can now navigate via links
6. to navigate via buttons use the routerLink directive and specify the paths.
7.to change the style of the active route use the routerlinkActive directive.


dynamic Grid layout
 implement oninit in the app.component.ts
 create a public list and set type to empty array
 create a public ngOnInIt and in the curly braces sepcify the value of "this.list" array
 create the objects for the grid and specify values
